  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Posttraumatic stress disorder (PTSD) is associated with poor health, high health care
      utilization, and an increased risk for a variety of somatic, inflammatory and autoimmune
      diseases. Research, including our own findings, indicates immunological alterations in PTSD
      patients. The aim of this study is to investigate whether alterations in the immune system of
      PTSD patients are reversible through a trauma-specific short-term therapy (Narrative Exposure
      Therapy).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
